  "content": "Sun & Rain Works holds a private archive documenting the March 30, 2009 work whose material is the act of Sotheby's Photographs auction itself, designated as artwork (The Auction as Artwork), together with its two artifact-parts: the born-digital website www.wtfisart.com and the auction performance work WTF is Ansel Adams. The archive is reported to contain photographs, born-digital and file metadata, emails, auction catalogue material, and receipts. The public Linked Art records name the work, the appropriated auction, and its parts; the primary evidence remains held by the studio pending redaction and rights review. No checksums, file hashes, or custody identifiers are published at this time; they will be added only when the underlying items are released.",
